le=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nlq1704964362863.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nlq1704964362863.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nlq1704964362863.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"our1665702612136\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Create a New Component\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Project Editor to create a new component.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"our1665702612136__context_w932ab1b5b1_w933ab1b5_w934ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"our1665702612136__topic_d11924e1_d11925e1_d11926e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n\t\tapplication definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n                 </div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5477e1_d5478e1_d5479e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Open the project to which the component will belong.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5480e1_d5481e1_d5482e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd stepresult\" id=\"our1665702612136__p_d11927e1_d11928e1_d11929e1\">In the Resource Browser, select the template for the type of component you want to create, and drag and drop it onto the project in the Project Structure Editor:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5483e1_d5484e1_d5485e1\">Dynamic Server Page component\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5486e1_d5487e1_d5488e1\">Entity Service component\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5489e1_d5490e1_d5491e1\">Form component\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5492e1_d5493e1_d5494e1\">Report component\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5495e1_d5496e1_d5497e1\">Service component\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5498e1_d5499e1_d5500e1\">Static Server Page component\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"our1665702612136__p_d11930e1_d11931e1_d11932e1\">The new object is created and assigned a temporary name.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5501e1_d5502e1_d5503e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd keypress\">Click the component name and enter a new name, then press <span class=\"ph keypress\">Enter</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5504e1_d5505e1_d5506e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd stepresult\" id=\"our1665702612136__p_d11933e1_d11934e1_d11935e1\">To open the component, right-click it and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span>.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"our1665702612136__p_d11936e1_d11937e1_d11938e1\">The component is opened in its own tab.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5507e1_d5508e1_d5509e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"our1665702612136__p_d11939e1_d11940e1_d11941e1\">Set the component properties in the Properties Inspector.\n Component properties define general component behavior, such as memory management and the use of a library. Component-specific properties determine characteristic or behavior that is only applicable to the specific type of component. For example, you can prevent your users from updating any data in a form component, whereas this is not applicable for service or report components.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"our1665702612136__p_d11942e1_d11943e1_d11944e1\">To begin with, you can accept the defaults and later go back to change properties as required.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"our1665702612136__result_w935ab1b5b5_w936ab1b5_w937ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"our1665702612136__topic_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5510e1_d5511e1_d5512e1\">For services, dynamic server pages, and static\n                  server pages: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zii1704964501123.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zii1704964501123.html\" title=\"For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure.\">Define the Component Structure</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"our1665702612136__li_d5513e1_d5514e1_d5515e1\">For form and report components: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cvl1690356504825.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvl1690356504825.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component.\">Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports</a>. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5755126\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5755126\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Create a New Component Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Create a New Component Use the Project Editor to create a new component. You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . Open the project to which the component will belong. In the Resource Browser, select the template for the type of component you want to create, and drag and drop it onto the project in the Project Structure Editor: Dynamic Server Page component Entity Service component Form component Report component Service component Static Server Page component The new object is created and assigned a temporary name. Click the component name and enter a new name, then press Enter . To open the component, right-click it and choose Open . The component is opened in its own tab. Set the component properties in the Properties Inspector. Component properties define general component behavior, such as memory management and the use of a library. Component-specific properties determine characteristic or behavior that is only applicable to the specific type of component. For example, you can prevent your users from updating any data in a form component, whereas this is not applicable for service or report components. To begin with, you can accept the defaults and later go back to change properties as required. For services, dynamic server pages, and static server pages: Define the Component Structure . For form and report components: Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}